Savage 1899/99 Lever Action .303 Sav, Ser. No. 21.510
This is a Savage Model 1899/99 rifle with a 26” barrel chambered for the .303 Savage cartridge. In 1920 Savage shortened the model number to “99”.  It is in very good mechanical condition with a good bore, a cartridge counter and a rectangular cocking indicator.  The Schnabel forend is very good, but the buttstock has been cut down and repaired (see photos).  The stock also has cracks near the receiver.  Vintage replacement stocks at Numrich Gun Parts and on eBay sell for $60 - $86.  Using Savage’s serial number look-up while leaving the decimal in, the manufacturing date comes up as 1895.  Inputting the number (21.510) without the decimal puts the date as 1901 or 1902.    $350.  Reply to this ad or contact John at 2 5 3 five four nine 6 6 one six.
